.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH dom 1  "dom "
.SH NAME
dom \- DOM inspection and manipulation
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdom\fR [\fB\-\-frame\fR] [\fB\-\-pierce\-shadow\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Query and manipulate the DOM: select elements by CSS selector or XPath, get/set attributes and text, read outerHTML, inspect computed styles, navigate the element tree, and remove elements. Target elements by node ID (from \*(Aqdom select\*(Aq), snapshot UID (from \*(Aqpage snapshot\*(Aq), or CSS selector (prefixed with \*(Aqcss:\*(Aq).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-frame\fR \fI<FRAME>\fR
Target frame by index, path (1/0), or \*(Aqauto\*(Aq
.TP
\fB\-\-pierce\-shadow\fR
Pierce open shadow DOM boundaries for element queries
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
dom\-select(1)
Select elements by CSS selector or XPath
.TP
dom\-get\-attribute(1)
Get a single attribute value from an element
.TP
dom\-get\-text(1)
Get the text content of an element
.TP
dom\-get\-html(1)
Get the outer HTML of an element
.TP
dom\-set\-attribute(1)
Set an attribute on an element
.TP
dom\-set\-text(1)
Set the text content of an element
.TP
dom\-remove(1)
Remove an element from the DOM
.TP
dom\-get\-style(1)
Get computed CSS styles of an element
.TP
dom\-set\-style(1)
Set the inline style of an element
.TP
dom\-parent(1)
Get the parent element
.TP
dom\-children(1)
List direct child elements
.TP
dom\-siblings(1)
List sibling elements
.TP
dom\-tree(1)
Pretty\-print the DOM tree
.TP
dom\-events(1)
List event listeners attached to an element
.TP
dom\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH EXTRA
EXAMPLES:
  # Select elements by CSS selector
  agentchrome dom select "h1"

  # Select by XPath
  agentchrome dom select "//a[@href]" \-\-xpath

  # Get an element\*(Aqs attribute
  agentchrome dom get\-attribute s3 href

  # Read element text
  agentchrome dom get\-text css:h1

  # Set an attribute
  agentchrome dom set\-attribute s5 class "highlight"

  # View the DOM tree
  agentchrome dom tree \-\-depth 3
.SH CAPABILITIES
.PP
DOM inspection and manipulation
.TP
.B dom select
Select elements by CSS selector or XPath
.TP
.B selector
CSS selector or XPath expression to query
.TP
.B --xpath
Interpret the selector as an XPath expression instead of CSS
.TP
.B dom get-attribute
Get a single attribute value from an element
.TP
.B node_id
Target element (node ID, UID like 's1', or CSS selector like 'css:#el')
.TP
.B attribute
Attribute name to read
.TP
.B dom get-text
Get the text content of an element
.TP
.B node_id
Target element (node ID, UID like 's1', or CSS selector like 'css:#el')
.TP
.B dom get-html
Get the outer HTML of an element
.TP
.B node_id
Target element (node ID, UID like 's1', or CSS selector like 'css:#el')
.TP
.B dom set-attribute
Set an attribute on an element
.TP
.B node_id
Target element (node ID, UID like 's1', or CSS selector like 'css:#el')
.TP
.B attribute
Attribute name to set
.TP
.B value
Attribute value
.TP
.B dom set-text
Set the text content of an element
.TP
.B node_id
Target element (node ID, UID like 's1', or CSS selector like 'css:#el')
.TP
.B text
Text content to set
.TP
.B dom remove
Remove an element from the DOM
.TP
.B node_id
Target element (node ID, UID like 's1', or CSS selector like 'css:#el')
.TP
.B dom get-style
Get computed CSS styles of an element
.TP
.B node_id
Target element (node ID, UID like 's1', or CSS selector like 'css:#el')
.TP
.B property
CSS property name (omit for all computed styles)
.TP
.B dom set-style
Set the inline style of an element
.TP
.B node_id
Target element (node ID, UID like 's1', or CSS selector like 'css:#el')
.TP
.B style
CSS style text (e.g. "color: red; font-size: 24px")
.TP
.B dom parent
Get the parent element
.TP
.B node_id
Target element (node ID, UID like 's1', or CSS selector like 'css:#el')
.TP
.B dom children
List direct child elements
.TP
.B node_id
Target element (node ID, UID like 's1', or CSS selector like 'css:#el')
.TP
.B dom siblings
List sibling elements
.TP
.B node_id
Target element (node ID, UID like 's1', or CSS selector like 'css:#el')
.TP
.B dom tree
Pretty-print the DOM tree
.TP
.B root_positional
Optional target element (node ID, UID, or CSS selector). Positional form of `--root`
.TP
.B --depth
Maximum tree depth to display
.TP
.B --root
Start the tree from a specific element (node ID, UID, or CSS selector)
.TP
.B dom events
List event listeners attached to an element
.TP
.B node_id
Target element (node ID, UID like 's1', or CSS selector like 'css:#el')
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Examples:
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dom select "h1"\`
Select elements by CSS selector
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dom select "//a[@href]" --xpath\`
Select elements by XPath expression
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dom get-attribute s3 href\`
Get an element's attribute by UID
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dom get-text css:h1\`
Get the text content of an element
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dom tree --depth 3\`
View the DOM tree with limited depth
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dom tree css:table --depth 3\`
View the DOM subtree rooted at an element (positional)
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dom --frame 1 select "css:button"\`
Query elements inside an iframe
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dom --pierce-shadow select "css:#shadow-btn"\`
Query elements inside shadow DOM
.TP
.B \`agentchrome dom events css:button\`
List event listeners on an element
